{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Belarus", "text_new": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Belarus}}\n{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Belarus\n| map1            = COVID-19 Cases in Belarus, 13.03.2020.png|thumb|\n| legend1         = Number of confirmed cases by region (as of 3 April):\n{{legend|#900000|100+ confirmed cases}}\n{{legend|#c80200|30\u201399 confirmed cases}}\n{{legend|#ee7070|4\u201329 confirmed cases}}\n{{legend|#ffc0c0|1\u20133 confirmed cases}}\n| disease         = [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Belarus]]\n| first_case      = [[Minsk]]\n| arrival_date    = 28 February 2020 <center>'''({{age in years, months and days|2020|02|28}})'''</center>\n| origin          = [[China]]\n| confirmed_cases = 562\n| suspected_cases = \n| recovery_cases  = 52\n| deaths          = 8\n| website         = \n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have spread to [[Belarus]], when the first case of COVID-19 in the country was registered in [[Minsk]] on 28 February 2020.<ref name=\"index_case_reuters\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-belarus-idUSKCN20M0IH|title=Belarus announces first case of coronavirus: TASS|date=2020-02-28|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-03-04|language=en}}</ref>\n__TOC__\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Belarus medical cases chart}}\nOn '''28 February''', Belarus confirmed its first case. A student from [[Iran]] tested positive on 27 February and was admitted to a hospital in Minsk.<ref name=\"minzdrav\">{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/sobytiya/v-belarusi-zaregistrirovan-zavoznoy-sluchay-koronavirusa/ |title=\u0423 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0456 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u044d\u0433\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043d\u044b \u0437\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0437\u043d\u044b \u0432\u044b\u043f\u0430\u0434\u0430\u043a \u043a\u0430\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0456\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |website=minzdrav.gov.by |language=ru |url-status=live |access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref><ref name=\"index_case_reuters\" /> The individual arrived in Belarus via a flight from [[Baku]], [[Azerbaijan]], on 22 February.<ref name=minzdrav /><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rferl.org/a/belarus-reports-first-confirmed-coronavirus-case/30459212.html |title=Four Lawmakers In Iran Test Positive As Coronavirus Forces Cancellation Of Friday Prayers |website=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty |language=en |access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref>\n\nAs of '''3 March''', there were 4 confirmed cases in Belarus.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/o-rezultatakh-testirovaniya-patsientov-na-koronavirus/ |title=minzdrav.gov.by |website=minzdrav.gov.by |language=ru |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316031614/https://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/o-rezultatakh-testirovaniya-patsientov-na-koronavirus/ |archive-date=2020-03-16 |access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref>\n\nOn '''4 March''', the [[Ministry of Health]] of Belarus confirmed 6 new cases of the disease: 4 cases in Minsk, 2 cases in [[Vitebsk]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/shest-sluchaev-koronavirusa-podtverzhdeno-v-belarusi/ |title=minzdrav.gov.by |website=minzdrav.gov.by |language=ru |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316031208/https://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/shest-sluchaev-koronavirusa-podtverzhdeno-v-belarusi/ |archive-date=2020-03-16 |access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref>\n\nOn '''13 March''', 27 cases were confirmed in [[Grodno]], [[Gomel]], Minsk, Vitebsk, and [[Minsk Oblast|Minsk Region]], including 5 students from the [[Faculty of International Relations, Belarusian State University|Faculty of International Relations]] of [[Belarusian State University]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://sputnik.by/health/20200313/1044173360/Minzdrav-prokommentiroval-massovuyu-gospitalizatsiyu-studentov-FMO-BGU.html |title=\u041c\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043a\u043e\u043c\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b \u043c\u0430\u0441\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0443\u044e \u0433\u043e\u0441\u043f\u0438\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0437\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044e \u0441\u0442\u0443\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0424\u041c\u041e \u0411\u0413\u0423}}</ref> Three patients were discharged from hospitals.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-health-coronavirus-belarus/belarus-has-27-cases-of-coronavirus-health-ministry-idUKKBN2101J4 |title=Belarus has 27 cases of coronavirus: health ministry |date=13 March 2020 |access-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316031858/https://uk.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-belarus/belarus-has-27-cases-of-coronavirus-health-ministry-idUKKBN2101J2 |archive-date=2020-03-16 |agency=Reuters}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=\u0413\u0443\u0448\u0442\u044b\u043d |first=\u0410\u0434\u0430\u0440'\u044f |url=https://news.tut.by/society/676262.html |title=\u041f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c \u0432 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0443\u0436\u0435 27 |date=13 March 2020 |work=Tut.by |access-date=13 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\nOn '''16 March''', the health ministry stated that the number of confirmed cases reached 36.<ref name=\"TASS_16Mar_36tot\">{{Cite news |url=https://tass.com/world/1130665 |title=Belarus registers 36 coronavirus cases, health ministry says |date=16 March 2020 |access-date=2020-03-16 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/NZBTl |archive-date=2020-03-16 |agency=TASS}}</ref> No new laboratory confirmed cases were reported on 17 March.<ref name=\"Masheka_0new_17March\">{{Cite news |url=https://masheka.by/belnews/4832-koronavirus-v-belarusi-situacija-na-17-marta.html |title=\u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438. \u0421\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044f \u043d\u0430 17 \u043c\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 |date=2020-03-17 |access-date=2020-03-17 |url-status=live <!-- live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317195709/https://masheka.by/belnews/4832-koronavirus-v-belarusi-situacija-na-17-marta.html |archive-date=2020-03-17 |language=ru |trans-title=Coronavirus in Belarus. The situation on 17 March.<!-- trans-title is the English translation --> |url-access=<!-- (subscription/registration/limited) default=free --> <!--|dead |unfit |usurped -->}}</ref>\n\nAs of '''18 March''', a total of 51 confirmed cases have been registered, including 5 recoveries and 37 cases of asymptomatic infection course.<ref name=\"minzdrav_18_March\">{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/situatsiya-s-koronavirusnoy-infektsiey-rastsenivaetsya-kak-kontroliruemaya/ |title=\u0421\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044f \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0435\u0439 \u0440\u0430\u0441\u0446\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0435\u0442\u0441\u044f, \u043a\u0430\u043a \u043a\u043e\u043d\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0435\u043c\u0430\u044f |date=18 March 2020 |website=minzdrav.gov.by |language=ru |access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"tut_51\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/676883.html |title=\u0412 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0444\u0438\u043a\u0441\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d 51 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |date=18 March 2020 |access-date=18 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nAs of '''20 March''', 69 cases have been registered, including 15 recoveries and 42 cases of asymptomatic infection course.<ref name=\"minzdrav_20_March\">{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/o-situatsii-po-covid-19/ |title=\u041e \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u043f\u043e COVID-19 |date=20 March 2020 |website=minzdrav.gov.by |language=ru |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"onliner_20_March\">{{Cite news |url=https://people.onliner.by/2020/03/20/virus-24 |title=\u0412 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0443\u0436\u0435 69 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0435\u0432 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430, 15 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0432\u044b\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u043d\u044b |date=20 March 2020 |access-date=20 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[Onliner.by]]}}</ref>\n\nAs of '''21 March''', a total of 76 confirmed cases have been reported.<ref name=\"onliner_21_March\">{{Cite news |url=https://people.onliner.by/2020/03/21/korona-14 |title=\u0412 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0443\u0436\u0435 76 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0435\u0432 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |date=21 March 2020 |access-date=21 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[Onliner.by]]}}</ref>\n\nAs of '''23 March''', 81 confirmed cases have been reported, including 22 recoveries. According to the [[COVID-19 testing#Testing statistics by country|official data]], more than 21,000 COVID-19 tests have been conducted in Belarus since 23 January.<ref name=\"onliner_23_March\">{{Cite news |url=https://people.onliner.by/2020/03/23/koronavirus-46 |title=\u0412 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0443\u0436\u0435 81 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |date=23 March 2020 |access-date=23 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[Onliner.by]]}}</ref><ref name=\"tut_81\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/677515.html |title=\u0412\u00a0\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0444\u0438\u043a\u0441\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d 81 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0439 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c, 22 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a\u0430 \u0443\u0436\u0435 \u0432\u044b\u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 |date=23 March 2020 |access-date=23 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nAs of '''25 March''', a total of 86 confirmed cases have been reported, including 29 recoveries.<ref name=\"tut_86\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/677858.html |title=\u0427\u0438\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c \u0432\u00a0\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0432\u044b\u0440\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0434\u043e\u00a086, \u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044b 29 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u0432 |date=25 March 2020 |access-date=25 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nAs of '''27 March''', a total of 94 confirmed cases have been reported, including 32 recoveries.<ref name=\"tut_94\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/678141.html |title=\u041a\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0435\u0432 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u0432\u00a0\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0432\u044b\u0440\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0434\u043e\u00a094 |date=27 March 2020 |access-date=27 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nAs of '''30 March''', a total of 152 confirmed cases have been reported, including 47 recoveries. More than 30,000 COVID-19 tests have been conducted to date since 23 January.<ref name=\"tut_152\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/678395.html |title=\u0412\u00a0\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 152 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u044f \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430, \u0432\u044b\u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 47 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a |date=30 March 2020 |access-date=30 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nOn '''31 March''', an officially unconfirmed death of a test-positive 75 years old patient in Vitebsk was reported by the media. Reportedly, the patient suffered from a chronic pulmonary decease.<ref name=\"tut_unofficial_death\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/678557.html |title=\u0412\u00a0\u0412\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0431\u0441\u043a\u0435 \u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u00a0\u043f\u043e\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u043c \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c |date=31 March 2020 |access-date=31 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref><ref name=\"onliner_unofficial_death\">{{Cite news |url=https://people.onliner.by/2020/03/31/koronavirus-56 |title=\u0412 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u044b\u0439 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c. \u041e\u0444\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043f\u043e\u043a\u0430 \u043d\u0435\u0442 |date=31 March 2020 |access-date=31 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[Onliner.by]]}}</ref><ref name=\"onliner_unofficial_death_colleagues\">{{Cite news |url=https://people.onliner.by/2020/03/31/teatr-12 |title=\"\u0423 \u043d\u0435\u0433\u043e \u0431\u044b\u043b\u043e \u0445\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043b\u0435\u0433\u043a\u0438\u0445\". \u041a\u043e\u043b\u043b\u0435\u0433\u0438 \u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0435\u0433\u043e \u043e\u0442 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u0440\u0430\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0437\u044b\u0432\u0430\u044e\u0442 \u043e \u043d\u0435\u043c |date=31 March 2020 |access-date=31 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[Onliner.by]]}}</ref> Later that day, the first case of death due to COVID-19 was confirmed by the Ministry of Health of Belarus.<ref name=\"minzdrav_first_death\">{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/sobytiya/v-belarusi-zaregistrirovan-zavoznoy-sluchay-koronavirusa/ |title=\u041e \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0441 COVID-19 \u0432 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 |date=31 March 2020 |website=minzdrav.gov.by |language=ru |access-date=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''1 April''', the second death of elderly COVID-19 patient with chronic deceases was reported by the Ministry of Health. According to the report, as of 1 April 2020, there were 163 COVID-19 cases registered in Belarus, including 2 deaths and ''at least'' 47 recoveries.<ref name=\"minzdrav_second_death\">{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/o-situatsii-s-covid-19-v-respublike-belarus/ |title=\u041e \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0441 COVID-19 \u0432 \u0420\u0435\u0441\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0435 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u044c |date=1 April 2020 |website=minzdrav.gov.by |language=ru |access-date=1 April 2020}}</ref> However, the ambiguity of the latest government reports has led to unofficial counting attempts, based on the official data, according to which the actual number of COVID-19 cases in Belarus could be as high as 217.<ref name=\"tut_unofficial_count\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/678770.html |title=\u041c\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432: \u0412\u00a0\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440 \u0432\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0439 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u0441\u00a0\u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c |date=1 April 2020 |access-date=1 April 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref> On that same day, the first COVID-19 case in [[Brest Region]] was reported by the officials.<ref name=\"tut_Brest_first_case\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/678855.html |title=\u0412\u00a0\u0411\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0432\u044b\u044f\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u044b\u0439 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442 c\u00a0\u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c |date=1 April 2020 |access-date=1 April 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nOn '''2 April''', the Ministry of Health of Belarus reported a total of 304 confirmed cases of COVID-19, including 254 active cases, 46 recoveries and 4 deaths. According to the report, 11 patents require [[assisted ventilation]] and  9,299 people remain under medical observation as first- and second-level contacts.<ref name=\"Ministry_2-04\">{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/o-situatsii-s-covid-19-bolshinstvo-sluchaev-vyyavlennye-kontakty-1-i-2-urovney/ |title=\u041e \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0441 COVID-19: \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448\u0438\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0435\u0432 - \u0432\u044b\u044f\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043d\u0442\u0430\u043a\u0442\u044b 1 \u0438 2 \u0443\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0435\u0439 |date=2 April 2020 |publisher=Ministry of Health of Belarus |language=ru |access-date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''3 April''', during a briefing of Ministry of Health officials for the press, a total of 351 confirmed cases were reported, including 190 in Minsk, 89 in [[Vitebsk Region]], 50 in Minsk Region, 13 in [[Gomel Region]], 6 in [[Grodno Region]], 2 in [[Mogilev Region]] and 1 in Brest Region. According to the officials, the majority of the COVID-19 patients are in 25 to 64 years old range.<ref name=\"tut_351\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/679145.html |title=\u041c\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432 \u0434\u0430\u043b \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0443 \u043f\u043e\u00a0\u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043c: \u0432\u00a0\u0442\u043e\u043f\u0435\u00a0\u2014 \u041c\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a \u0438\u00a0\u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u044c, \u0430\u00a0\u0442\u0430\u043a\u0436\u0435 \u0412\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0431\u0449\u0438\u043d\u0430, \u0432\u0441\u0435\u0433\u043e 351 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0439 |date=3 April 2020 |access-date=3 April 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nOn '''4 April''', a total of 440 confirmed cases have been reported, including 41 recovery and 5 deaths. According to the media, the declining number of recoveries is due to changes in the counting methodology used by the officials: prior to 30 March, both discharged and \"preparing to be discharged\" patients were reported as recovered; after the 30 March, only the discharged patients are counted as recovered.<ref name=\"tut_440\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/679260.html |title=\u0427\u0438\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c \u0432\u00a0\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0432\u044b\u0440\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0434\u043e\u00a0440. \u041c\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0438\u043b \u0441\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0442\u044c 5 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a |date=4 April 2020 |access-date=4 April 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nOn '''5 April''', a total of 562 confirmed cases have been reported, including 52 recoveries and 8 deaths.<ref name=\"tut_562\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/679313.html |title=\n\u0427\u0438\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c \u0432\u00a0\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0432\u044b\u0440\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0434\u043e\u00a0562. \u041c\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0438\u043b \u0441\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0442\u044c 8 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a |date=5 April 2020 |access-date=5 April 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref><ref name=\"minzdrav_562\">{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/soobshchenie-press-sluzhby/ |title=\u0421\u043e\u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0441-\u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u044b |date=5 April 2020 |publisher=minzdrav.gov.by |language=ru |access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Government response ==\nOn 16 March 2020, [[president of Belarus]], [[Alexander Lukashenko]], dismissed the threat of coronavirus and encouraged working in fields and driving [[tractor]]s as a way of overcoming the pandemic: \"You just have to work, especially now, in a village [...] there, the tractor will heal everyone. The fields heal everyone\".<ref name=\"Lukashenko_tractors\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/16/belarussian-leader-proposes-tractor-therapy-for-coronavirus-a69644 |title=Belarussian Leader Proposes 'Tractor' Therapy For Coronavirus |date=16 March 2020 |website=[[The Moscow Times]] |access-date=2 April 2020}}</ref> In his further comments on the pandemic, the Belarussian leader referred to it as \"psychosis\" and, on 28 March, played a game of hockey, later stating in an interview \"it is better to die on our feet, than live on your knees [...] sport, especially on ice, is better than any antiviral medication, it is the real thing\".<ref name=\"Lukashenko_hockey\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/hockey/2020/03/31/belarus-president-plays-hockey-calls-fear-coronavirus-psychosis/5093894002/ |title=Belarus president plays hockey, says global coronavirus measures are result of 'psychosis' |date=31 March 2020 |website=[[The Moscow Times]] |access-date=2 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"onliner_hockey\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/678474.html |title=\u041b\u0443\u043a\u0430\u0448\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e: \"\u0425\u043e\u043a\u043a\u0435\u0439 \u2014 \u043b\u0443\u0447\u0448\u0435\u0435 \u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0435 \u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e!\" |date=28 March 2020 |access-date=2 April 2020 |language=ru |website=[[onliner.by]]}}</ref> Prior to that, in an official meeting, Lukashenko proposed \"poisoning\" the coronavirus with [[vodka]], as well as attending [[Banya (sauna)|banyas]] as the best cure for the disease.<ref name=\"cnn_vodka_banya\">{{Cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/30/europe/soviet-strongmen-coronavirus-intl/index.html |title=Post-Soviet strongmen prescribe vodka, hockey and folk medicine against coronavirus |date=31 March 2020 |access-date=2 April 2020 |website=[[CNN]]}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 March 2020, a mandatory 14-day self-[[quarantine]] requirement was instituted for persons entering Belarus from countries affected by the pandemic, with the exception of diplomats and their families, air crews and persons transiting Belarus on return to their home countries.<ref name=\"quarantine_gov\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.government.by/ru/content/9339 |title=\u041e \u043c\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0445 \u043f\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0442\u0432\u0440\u0430\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044e \u0437\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0437\u0430 \u0438 \u0440\u0430\u0441\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0438, \u0432\u044b\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c COVID-19 |date=30 March 2020 |website=government.by |language=ru |access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nAs of 30 March, Belarus has not initiated a nation-wide quarantine effort.<ref name=\"tut_152\" /> That, as well as the gradual decrease in transparency of the official reports on the pandemic, led to criticism from the press and population, emphasizing absence of the up-to-date information about the territories affected by the virus, decreased update frequency and increased ambiguity of the official reports, as well as restraint of the non-governmental media from the government sessions on the epidemiological situation in the country.<ref name=\"tut_transparency_letter\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/678474.html |title=\u041f\u043e\u0447\u0435\u043c\u0443 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044f \u043e\u00a0\u0440\u0430\u0441\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u0432\u00a0\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0434\u043e\u043b\u0436\u043d\u0430 \u0431\u044b\u0442\u044c \u043c\u0430\u043a\u0441\u0438\u043c\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e \u043e\u0442\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0442\u043e\u0439. \u041e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0440\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0438 TUT.BY |date=30 March 2020 |access-date=30 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 April, a one-week extension of spring vacation for schools was announced by the Ministry of Education of Belarus.<ref name=\"vacation_extended\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/679125.html |title=\u0412\u0435\u0441\u0435\u043d\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043a\u0430\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0443\u043b\u044b \u0443\u00a0\u0448\u043a\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432 \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0443\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043b\u0435\u043d\u044b \u043d\u0430\u00a0\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0443 \u043d\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043b\u044e\u00a0\u2014 \u0434\u043e\u00a013\u00a0\u0430\u043f\u0440\u0435\u043b\u044f |date=4 April 2020 |access-date=4 April 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\n== Economic impact ==\nOn 30 March 2020, Belarus and [[International Monetary Fund|IMF]] started negotiations on the $900 million loan intended to compensate the economic losses from the coronavirus pandemic.<ref name=\"tut_IMF_load\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/economics/678483.html |title=\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u044c \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0438\u0442 \u0443\u00a0\u041c\u0412\u0424 \"\u0431\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0440\u044b\u0439\" \u043a\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0442 \u043d\u0430\u00a0\u0431\u043e\u0440\u044c\u0431\u0443 \u0441\u00a0\u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0438\u044f\u043c\u0438 \u0433\u043b\u043e\u0431\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043a\u0440\u0438\u0437\u0438\u0441\u0430 |date=30 March 2020 |access-date=30 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://gisanddata.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6 Coronavirus COVID-19 Global Cases] and [https://github.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19 historical data] by [[Johns Hopkins University]]\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Belarus]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Belarus}}\n{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Belarus\n| map1            = COVID-19 Cases in Belarus, 13.03.2020.png|thumb|\n| legend1         = Number of confirmed cases by region (as of 3 April):\n{{legend|#900000|100+ confirmed cases}}\n{{legend|#c80200|30\u201399 confirmed cases}}\n{{legend|#ee7070|4\u201329 confirmed cases}}\n{{legend|#ffc0c0|1\u20133 confirmed cases}}\n| disease         = [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Belarus]]\n| first_case      = [[Minsk]]\n| arrival_date    = 28 February 2020 <center><b>({{age in years, months and days|2020|02|28}})</b></center>\n| origin          = [[China]]\n| confirmed_cases = 562\n| suspected_cases = \n| recovery_cases  = 52\n| deaths          = 8\n| website         = \n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have spread to [[Belarus]], when the first case of COVID-19 in the country was registered in [[Minsk]] on 28 February 2020.<ref name=\"index_case_reuters\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-belarus-idUSKCN20M0IH|title=Belarus announces first case of coronavirus: TASS|date=2020-02-28|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-03-04|language=en}}</ref>\n__TOC__\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Belarus medical cases chart}}\nOn '''28 February''', Belarus confirmed its first case. A student from [[Iran]] tested positive on 27 February and was admitted to a hospital in Minsk.<ref name=\"minzdrav\">{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/sobytiya/v-belarusi-zaregistrirovan-zavoznoy-sluchay-koronavirusa/ |title=\u0423 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0456 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u044d\u0433\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043d\u044b \u0437\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0437\u043d\u044b \u0432\u044b\u043f\u0430\u0434\u0430\u043a \u043a\u0430\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0456\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |website=minzdrav.gov.by |language=ru |url-status=live |access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref><ref name=\"index_case_reuters\" /> The individual arrived in Belarus via a flight from [[Baku]], [[Azerbaijan]], on 22 February.<ref name=minzdrav /><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rferl.org/a/belarus-reports-first-confirmed-coronavirus-case/30459212.html |title=Four Lawmakers In Iran Test Positive As Coronavirus Forces Cancellation Of Friday Prayers |website=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty |language=en |access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref>\n\nAs of '''3 March''', there were 4 confirmed cases in Belarus.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/o-rezultatakh-testirovaniya-patsientov-na-koronavirus/ |title=minzdrav.gov.by |website=minzdrav.gov.by |language=ru |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316031614/https://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/o-rezultatakh-testirovaniya-patsientov-na-koronavirus/ |archive-date=2020-03-16 |access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref>\n\nOn '''4 March''', the [[Ministry of Health]] of Belarus confirmed 6 new cases of the disease: 4 cases in Minsk, 2 cases in [[Vitebsk]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/shest-sluchaev-koronavirusa-podtverzhdeno-v-belarusi/ |title=minzdrav.gov.by |website=minzdrav.gov.by |language=ru |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316031208/https://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/shest-sluchaev-koronavirusa-podtverzhdeno-v-belarusi/ |archive-date=2020-03-16 |access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref>\n\nOn '''13 March''', 27 cases were confirmed in [[Grodno]], [[Gomel]], Minsk, Vitebsk, and [[Minsk Oblast|Minsk Region]], including 5 students from the [[Faculty of International Relations, Belarusian State University|Faculty of International Relations]] of [[Belarusian State University]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://sputnik.by/health/20200313/1044173360/Minzdrav-prokommentiroval-massovuyu-gospitalizatsiyu-studentov-FMO-BGU.html |title=\u041c\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043a\u043e\u043c\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b \u043c\u0430\u0441\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0443\u044e \u0433\u043e\u0441\u043f\u0438\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0437\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044e \u0441\u0442\u0443\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0424\u041c\u041e \u0411\u0413\u0423}}</ref> Three patients were discharged from hospitals.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-health-coronavirus-belarus/belarus-has-27-cases-of-coronavirus-health-ministry-idUKKBN2101J4 |title=Belarus has 27 cases of coronavirus: health ministry |date=13 March 2020 |access-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316031858/https://uk.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-belarus/belarus-has-27-cases-of-coronavirus-health-ministry-idUKKBN2101J2 |archive-date=2020-03-16 |agency=Reuters}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=\u0413\u0443\u0448\u0442\u044b\u043d |first=\u0410\u0434\u0430\u0440'\u044f |url=https://news.tut.by/society/676262.html |title=\u041f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c \u0432 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0443\u0436\u0435 27 |date=13 March 2020 |work=Tut.by |access-date=13 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\nOn '''16 March''', the health ministry stated that the number of confirmed cases reached 36.<ref name=\"TASS_16Mar_36tot\">{{Cite news |url=https://tass.com/world/1130665 |title=Belarus registers 36 coronavirus cases, health ministry says |date=16 March 2020 |access-date=2020-03-16 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/NZBTl |archive-date=2020-03-16 |agency=TASS}}</ref> No new laboratory confirmed cases were reported on 17 March.<ref name=\"Masheka_0new_17March\">{{Cite news |url=https://masheka.by/belnews/4832-koronavirus-v-belarusi-situacija-na-17-marta.html |title=\u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438. \u0421\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044f \u043d\u0430 17 \u043c\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 |date=2020-03-17 |access-date=2020-03-17 |url-status=live <!-- live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317195709/https://masheka.by/belnews/4832-koronavirus-v-belarusi-situacija-na-17-marta.html |archive-date=2020-03-17 |language=ru |trans-title=Coronavirus in Belarus. The situation on 17 March.<!-- trans-title is the English translation --> |url-access=<!-- (subscription/registration/limited) default=free --> <!--|dead |unfit |usurped -->}}</ref>\n\nAs of '''18 March''', a total of 51 confirmed cases have been registered, including 5 recoveries and 37 cases of asymptomatic infection course.<ref name=\"minzdrav_18_March\">{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/situatsiya-s-koronavirusnoy-infektsiey-rastsenivaetsya-kak-kontroliruemaya/ |title=\u0421\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044f \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0435\u0439 \u0440\u0430\u0441\u0446\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0435\u0442\u0441\u044f, \u043a\u0430\u043a \u043a\u043e\u043d\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0435\u043c\u0430\u044f |date=18 March 2020 |website=minzdrav.gov.by |language=ru |access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"tut_51\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/676883.html |title=\u0412 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0444\u0438\u043a\u0441\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d 51 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |date=18 March 2020 |access-date=18 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nAs of '''20 March''', 69 cases have been registered, including 15 recoveries and 42 cases of asymptomatic infection course.<ref name=\"minzdrav_20_March\">{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/o-situatsii-po-covid-19/ |title=\u041e \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u043f\u043e COVID-19 |date=20 March 2020 |website=minzdrav.gov.by |language=ru |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"onliner_20_March\">{{Cite news |url=https://people.onliner.by/2020/03/20/virus-24 |title=\u0412 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0443\u0436\u0435 69 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0435\u0432 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430, 15 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0432\u044b\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u043d\u044b |date=20 March 2020 |access-date=20 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[Onliner.by]]}}</ref>\n\nAs of '''21 March''', a total of 76 confirmed cases have been reported.<ref name=\"onliner_21_March\">{{Cite news |url=https://people.onliner.by/2020/03/21/korona-14 |title=\u0412 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0443\u0436\u0435 76 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0435\u0432 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |date=21 March 2020 |access-date=21 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[Onliner.by]]}}</ref>\n\nAs of '''23 March''', 81 confirmed cases have been reported, including 22 recoveries. According to the [[COVID-19_testing#Testing_statistics_by_country|official data]], more than 21,000 COVID-19 tests have been conducted in Belarus since 23 January.<ref name=\"onliner_23_March\">{{Cite news |url=https://people.onliner.by/2020/03/23/koronavirus-46 |title=\u0412 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0443\u0436\u0435 81 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |date=23 March 2020 |access-date=23 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[Onliner.by]]}}</ref><ref name=\"tut_81\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/677515.html |title=\u0412\u00a0\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0444\u0438\u043a\u0441\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d 81 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0439 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c, 22 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a\u0430 \u0443\u0436\u0435 \u0432\u044b\u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 |date=23 March 2020 |access-date=23 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nAs of '''25 March''', a total of 86 confirmed cases have been reported, including 29 recoveries.<ref name=\"tut_86\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/677858.html |title=\u0427\u0438\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c \u0432\u00a0\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0432\u044b\u0440\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0434\u043e\u00a086, \u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044b 29 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u0432 |date=25 March 2020 |access-date=25 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nAs of '''27 March''', a total of 94 confirmed cases have been reported, including 32 recoveries.<ref name=\"tut_94\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/678141.html |title=\u041a\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0435\u0432 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u0432\u00a0\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0432\u044b\u0440\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0434\u043e\u00a094 |date=27 March 2020 |access-date=27 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nAs of '''30 March''', a total of 152 confirmed cases have been reported, including 47 recoveries. More than 30,000 COVID-19 tests have been conducted to date since 23 January.<ref name=\"tut_152\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/678395.html |title=\u0412\u00a0\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 152 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u044f \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430, \u0432\u044b\u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 47 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a |date=30 March 2020 |access-date=30 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nOn '''31 March''', an officially unconfirmed death of a test-positive 75 years old patient in Vitebsk was reported by the media. Reportedly, the patient suffered from a chronic pulmonary decease.<ref name=\"tut_unofficial_death\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/678557.html |title=\u0412\u00a0\u0412\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0431\u0441\u043a\u0435 \u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u00a0\u043f\u043e\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u043c \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c |date=31 March 2020 |access-date=31 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref><ref name=\"onliner_unofficial_death\">{{Cite news |url=https://people.onliner.by/2020/03/31/koronavirus-56 |title=\u0412 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u044b\u0439 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c. \u041e\u0444\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043f\u043e\u043a\u0430 \u043d\u0435\u0442 |date=31 March 2020 |access-date=31 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[Onliner.by]]}}</ref><ref name=\"onliner_unofficial_death_colleagues\">{{Cite news |url=https://people.onliner.by/2020/03/31/teatr-12 |title=\"\u0423 \u043d\u0435\u0433\u043e \u0431\u044b\u043b\u043e \u0445\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043b\u0435\u0433\u043a\u0438\u0445\". \u041a\u043e\u043b\u043b\u0435\u0433\u0438 \u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0435\u0433\u043e \u043e\u0442 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u0440\u0430\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0437\u044b\u0432\u0430\u044e\u0442 \u043e \u043d\u0435\u043c |date=31 March 2020 |access-date=31 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[Onliner.by]]}}</ref> Later that day, the first case of death due to COVID-19 was confirmed by the Ministry of Health of Belarus.<ref name=\"minzdrav_first_death\">{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/sobytiya/v-belarusi-zaregistrirovan-zavoznoy-sluchay-koronavirusa/ |title=\u041e \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0441 COVID-19 \u0432 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 |date=31 March 2020 |website=minzdrav.gov.by |language=ru |access-date=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''1 April''', the second death of elderly COVID-19 patient with chronic deceases was reported by the Ministry of Health. According to the report, as of 1 April 2020, there were 163 COVID-19 cases registered in Belarus, including 2 deaths and ''at least'' 47 recoveries.<ref name=\"minzdrav_second_death\">{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/o-situatsii-s-covid-19-v-respublike-belarus/ |title=\u041e \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0441 COVID-19 \u0432 \u0420\u0435\u0441\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0435 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u044c |date=1 April 2020 |website=minzdrav.gov.by |language=ru |access-date=1 April 2020}}</ref> However, the ambiguity of the latest government reports has led to unofficial counting attempts, based on the official data, according to which the actual number of COVID-19 cases in Belarus could be as high as 217.<ref name=\"tut_unofficial_count\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/678770.html |title=\u041c\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432: \u0412\u00a0\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440 \u0432\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0439 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u0441\u00a0\u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c |date=1 April 2020 |access-date=1 April 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref> On that same day, the first COVID-19 case in [[Brest Region]] was reported by the officials.<ref name=\"tut_Brest_first_case\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/678855.html |title=\u0412\u00a0\u0411\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0432\u044b\u044f\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u044b\u0439 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442 c\u00a0\u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c |date=1 April 2020 |access-date=1 April 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nOn '''2 April''', the Ministry of Health of Belarus reported a total of 304 confirmed cases of COVID-19, including 254 active cases, 46 recoveries and 4 deaths. According to the report, 11 patents require [[assisted ventilation]] and  9,299 people remain under medical observation as first- and second-level contacts.<ref name=\"Ministry_2-04\">{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/o-situatsii-s-covid-19-bolshinstvo-sluchaev-vyyavlennye-kontakty-1-i-2-urovney/ |title=\u041e \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0441 COVID-19: \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448\u0438\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0435\u0432 - \u0432\u044b\u044f\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043d\u0442\u0430\u043a\u0442\u044b 1 \u0438 2 \u0443\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0435\u0439 |date=2 April 2020 |publisher=Ministry of Health of Belarus |language=ru |access-date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''3 April''', during a briefing of Ministry of Health officials for the press, a total of 351 confirmed cases were reported, including 190 in Minsk, 89 in [[Vitebsk Region]], 50 in Minsk Region, 13 in [[Gomel Region]], 6 in [[Grodno Region]], 2 in [[Mogilev Region]] and 1 in Brest Region. According to the officials, the majority of the COVID-19 patients are in 25 to 64 years old range.<ref name=\"tut_351\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/679145.html |title=\u041c\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432 \u0434\u0430\u043b \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0443 \u043f\u043e\u00a0\u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043c: \u0432\u00a0\u0442\u043e\u043f\u0435\u00a0\u2014 \u041c\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a \u0438\u00a0\u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u044c, \u0430\u00a0\u0442\u0430\u043a\u0436\u0435 \u0412\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0431\u0449\u0438\u043d\u0430, \u0432\u0441\u0435\u0433\u043e 351 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0439 |date=3 April 2020 |access-date=3 April 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nOn '''4 April''', a total of 440 confirmed cases have been reported, including 41 recovery and 5 deaths. According to the media, the declining number of recoveries is due to changes in the counting methodology used by the officials: prior to 30 March, both discharged and \"preparing to be discharged\" patients were reported as recovered; after the 30 March, only the discharged patients are counted as recovered.<ref name=\"tut_440\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/679260.html |title=\u0427\u0438\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c \u0432\u00a0\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0432\u044b\u0440\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0434\u043e\u00a0440. \u041c\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0438\u043b \u0441\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0442\u044c 5 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a |date=4 April 2020 |access-date=4 April 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nOn '''5 April''', a total of 562 confirmed cases have been reported, including 52 recoveries and 8 deaths.<ref name=\"tut_562\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/679313.html |title=\n\u0427\u0438\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c \u0432\u00a0\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0432\u044b\u0440\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0434\u043e\u00a0562. \u041c\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0438\u043b \u0441\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0442\u044c 8 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a |date=5 April 2020 |access-date=5 April 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref><ref name=\"minzdrav_562\">{{Cite web |url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/ru/sobytiya/soobshchenie-press-sluzhby/ |title=\u0421\u043e\u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0441-\u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u044b |date=5 April 2020 |publisher=minzdrav.gov.by |language=ru |access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Government response ==\nOn 16 March 2020, [[president of Belarus]], [[Alexander Lukashenko]], dismissed the threat of coronavirus and encouraged working in fields and driving [[tractor]]s as a way of overcoming the pandemic: \"You just have to work, especially now, in a village [...] there, the tractor will heal everyone. The fields heal everyone\".<ref name=\"Lukashenko_tractors\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/16/belarussian-leader-proposes-tractor-therapy-for-coronavirus-a69644 |title=Belarussian Leader Proposes 'Tractor' Therapy For Coronavirus |date=16 March 2020 |website=[[The Moscow Times]] |access-date=2 April 2020}}</ref> In his further comments on the pandemic, the Belarussian leader referred to it as \"psychosis\" and, on 28 March, played a game of hockey, later stating in an interview \"it is better to die on our feet, than live on your knees [...] sport, especially on ice, is better than any antiviral medication, it is the real thing\".<ref name=\"Lukashenko_hockey\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/hockey/2020/03/31/belarus-president-plays-hockey-calls-fear-coronavirus-psychosis/5093894002/ |title=Belarus president plays hockey, says global coronavirus measures are result of 'psychosis' |date=31 March 2020 |website=[[The Moscow Times]] |access-date=2 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"onliner_hockey\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/678474.html |title=\u041b\u0443\u043a\u0430\u0448\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e: \u00ab\u0425\u043e\u043a\u043a\u0435\u0439 \u2014 \u043b\u0443\u0447\u0448\u0435\u0435 \u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0435 \u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e!\u00bb |date=28 March 2020 |access-date=2 April 2020 |language=ru |website=[[onliner.by]]}}</ref> Prior to that, in an official meeting, Lukashenko proposed \"poisoning\" the coronavirus with [[vodka]], as well as attending [[Banya (sauna)|banyas]] as the best cure for the disease.<ref name=\"cnn_vodka_banya\">{{Cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/30/europe/soviet-strongmen-coronavirus-intl/index.html |title=Post-Soviet strongmen prescribe vodka, hockey and folk medicine against coronavirus |date=31 March 2020 |access-date=2 April 2020 |website=[[CNN]]}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 March 2020, a mandatory 14-day self-[[quarantine]] requirement was instituted for persons entering Belarus from countries affected by the pandemic, with the exception of diplomats and their families, air crews and persons transiting Belarus on return to their home countries.<ref name=\"quarantine_gov\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.government.by/ru/content/9339 |title=\u041e \u043c\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0445 \u043f\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0442\u0432\u0440\u0430\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044e \u0437\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0437\u0430 \u0438 \u0440\u0430\u0441\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0438, \u0432\u044b\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c COVID-19 |date=30 March 2020 |website=government.by |language=ru |access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nAs of 30 March, Belarus has not initiated a nation-wide quarantine effort.<ref name=\"tut_152\" /> That, as well as the gradual decrease in transparency of the official reports on the pandemic, led to criticism from the press and population, emphasizing absence of the up-to-date information about the territories affected by the virus, decreased update frequency and increased ambiguity of the official reports, as well as restraint of the non-governmental media from the government sessions on the epidemiological situation in the country.<ref name=\"tut_transparency_letter\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/678474.html |title=\u041f\u043e\u0447\u0435\u043c\u0443 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044f \u043e\u00a0\u0440\u0430\u0441\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u0432\u00a0\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0434\u043e\u043b\u0436\u043d\u0430 \u0431\u044b\u0442\u044c \u043c\u0430\u043a\u0441\u0438\u043c\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e \u043e\u0442\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0442\u043e\u0439. \u041e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0440\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0438 TUT.BY |date=30 March 2020 |access-date=30 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 April, a one-week extension of spring vacation for schools was announced by the Ministry of Education of Belarus.<ref name=\"vacation_extended\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/society/679125.html |title=\u0412\u0435\u0441\u0435\u043d\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043a\u0430\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0443\u043b\u044b \u0443\u00a0\u0448\u043a\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432 \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0443\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043b\u0435\u043d\u044b \u043d\u0430\u00a0\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0443 \u043d\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043b\u044e\u00a0\u2014 \u0434\u043e\u00a013\u00a0\u0430\u043f\u0440\u0435\u043b\u044f |date=4 April 2020 |access-date=4 April 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\n== Economic impact ==\nOn 30 March 2020, Belarus and [[International Monetary Fund|IMF]] started negotiations on the $900 million loan intended to compensate the economic losses from the coronavirus pandemic.<ref name=\"tut_IMF_load\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.tut.by/economics/678483.html |title=\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u044c \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0438\u0442 \u0443\u00a0\u041c\u0412\u0424 \"\u0431\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0440\u044b\u0439\" \u043a\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0442 \u043d\u0430\u00a0\u0431\u043e\u0440\u044c\u0431\u0443 \u0441\u00a0\u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0438\u044f\u043c\u0438 \u0433\u043b\u043e\u0431\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043a\u0440\u0438\u0437\u0438\u0441\u0430 |date=30 March 2020 |access-date=30 March 2020 |language=ru |website=[[tut.by]]}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://gisanddata.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6 Coronavirus COVID-19 Global Cases] and [https://github.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19 historical data] by [[Johns Hopkins University]]\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Belarus ]]\n", "name_user": "Joeykai", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Belarus"}
